The paper proposes a technique for automatically synthesizing regular expressions using a combination of examples and natural language. This involves parsing the English description into a hierarchical sketch and using a programming-by-example (PBE) engine to prioritize the search and make deductions for pruning the search space. This work involves techniques from programming languages (PL), artificial intelligence (AI), software engineering (SE), computational linguistics (CL), and machine learning (LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL, followed by cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
